12:02.618 --> 12:06.544
what I had done for those little Mexican children. 
Because you taught in a minority program. I

12:08.828 --> 12:09.769
certainly did. You went straight to do that. 
That's all I did. Right. Now, what school was that

12:14.036 --> 12:16.119
that you taught in? Well, I first started out in 
John F. Kennedy in San Antonio. Okay. And, well, it

12:22.349 --> 12:25.213
was all in Edgewood District. Edgewood, right. 
And that's the poorest district there in San

12:26.054 --> 12:30.461
Antonio. Right. And Stani, Stano, uh...

12:37.617 --> 13:02.697
steinheiser

12:37.617 --> 13:02.697
was my principal and he was the best thing to me that 
ever was and he knew that i had that little mexican

12:37.617 --> 13:02.697
feelings at heart and he he did everything he could 
to help me he was a good man yeah and i'm not sorry for

12:37.617 --> 13:02.697
for working as hard as i did i'd do it again tomorrow 
you drove Before you moved to San Antonio, I know

13:03.503 --> 13:07.288
how you got your education. Did you just stop 
planting tomatoes one day and made a decision you

13:07.929 --> 13:12.715
were going to do something? I said that was the 
hardest work I ever did in my life, and I could make a

13:12.815 --> 13:24.651
living a lot easier than I could working two acres 
of tomatoes with a hoe. So I bundled up my little

13:24.833 --> 13:33.186
self and went to San Marcos in the summer of 48. And I 
started out with 12 hours that I had gotten back in

13:33.447 --> 13:40.979
19 and 23 and 24. And that was two hour courses at a 
time. That's all the college credits that I had.

13:51.074 --> 13:54.899
Got a certificate standing for it that summer. 
That type, yeah. You know, that type. Well, I got a

13:58.043 --> 14:03.870
four-year certificate because I made an average 
of 85 on all my courses. Well, anyway, a six-year

14:04.791 --> 14:08.075
certificate. That's what it was. If you make an 
average of 85, you get a six-year. And if you make an

14:11.840 --> 14:14.884
average of 75, you get a four-year. Minus 85, thank 
goodness. I did have a little sense then. So

14:18.969 --> 14:20.811
anyway. I got my certificate. I enrolled in the 
fall semester. I taught school every day and went

14:25.598 --> 14:30.886
to school every night. And in 1950, I walked down 
the aisle with my BS degree. And I taught school

14:38.577 --> 14:40.420
every day. And 1952, I got my master's degree. But I 
took it easy. I just didn't go every night to

14:49.558 --> 14:51.741
school. You went? On Saturdays. You went to school 
on Saturdays. Every Saturday. In order to get your

14:57.990 --> 14:58.891
master's degree. To get my master's degree. And 
you did that at Trinity, though, didn't you? At San

15:02.316 --> 15:04.038
Antonio. I got my BS degree at Trinity and my 
master's degree at St. Mark's.

15:12.496 --> 15:16.525
But I want to tell you right now, I took work at the 
University of Texas. I took work at Lubbock. I took

15:18.509 --> 15:26.927
work at Arkansas and Sam Houston, A&M.

15:29.759 --> 15:30.720
I believe that's all. And the hardest school of all 
of them is Trinity University. Don't kid

15:34.765 --> 15:36.327
yourself. You've really got to get out and get with 
it. Oh, I did too. I took some Bible study out at the

15:41.132 --> 15:45.857
Lady of the Lake. I'll tell you that. I took history 
of the Bible, and that made me sit up and take

15:48.260 --> 15:54.047
notice. Then I took the Old Testament. Then I took 
the New Testament.

16:00.117 --> 16:01.800
I've had it. And it was hard. But in order to 
understand our history, if you don't understand

16:03.903 --> 16:19.868
the Jewish or Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob's laws and 
the beginning of this thing, it's just hard for you

16:03.903 --> 16:19.868
to ever get it down. Well, that's something I want 
to ask you about religion. I'm aware that in

16:24.576 --> 16:26.479
Texas... We have a new religion, and it's the New 
Testament. But the old-time religions in Texas

16:30.250 --> 16:34.497
didn't just start there. They began in the 
beginning. God created the earth and taught

16:36.700 --> 16:40.526
through Genesis on up. And I wonder if today's 
religion isn't short-sighting itself, because

16:40.546 --> 16:50.320
this community is still an old community. And I 
know it's an Old Testament community. Well, it's

16:55.248 --> 16:59.893
just, I think that's the reason most of these broke 
off from the Methodist Church. It's still the old

16:59.993 --> 17:03.196
Methodist Church. I can remember, as a little 
girl, we came in the Methodist Church, we knelt.

17:10.044 --> 17:11.185
That was God's house. And we came in. We were quiet. 
And we knelt. We went to our pew. We knelt. We made

17:19.126 --> 17:23.171
the sign of the cross and we said our prayer while we 
were there. It was quietly said, but we said it.

17:27.336 --> 17:29.379
There was a cross up in the front. We knew what that 
cross signified. Today, you just walk in that

17:33.203 --> 17:41.834
church and they start talking and they visit and 
they yak, yak, yak. That I just cannot take. That is

17:46.058 --> 17:47.259
sacred. And in the temple, don't you remember, 
they were cast out because they did that? And I

17:51.984 --> 17:53.245
can't tell. There's something in me that boils up 
that I can't help. I know. And I like to go to the

17:59.271 --> 18:06.157
Pentecostal church and hear them because they do 
have lots of good services. But I can't stand the

18:06.698 --> 18:13.745
screaming because in the beginning, God said that 
couldn't be. Yeah. And in the temple, when they

18:15.168 --> 18:21.535
began to carry on like that, they were let out. And I 
guess I'm just, I don't know what's wrong with me.

18:28.363 --> 18:31.767
How do you feel that things have a sacredness? 
There's a sacredness that I can't get away from.

18:36.412 --> 18:37.453
And I know one thing. I got up and walked out of 
church one time, and I don't think I was over it. six

18:43.450 --> 19:06.589
or seven years old of course we didn't have such 
things the bathroom but i had to tinkle and i got up

18:43.450 --> 19:06.589
and walked out of the church and my daddy just 
blistered my little seat good because i didn't

18:43.450 --> 19:06.589
whisper to him and tell him that i needed to go to the 
bathroom i got up and walked out of the church and

